(C) Hyper IgM syndrome is characterized by normal or elevated levels of IgM and low levels of other immunoglobulins. Flow cytometry can be used to identify defects in CD40 ligand expression on T cells.

(D) Severe combined immunodeficiency disease (SCID) involves a severe defect in both T and B lymphocyte systems. Flow cytometry can be used to identify the absence or very low levels of T cells (CD3+), B cells (CD19+), and sometimes NK cells (CD16+/CD56+).
